JOHANNESBURG – Age-cheating is not a new phenomenon in South African football, in fact, it still seems to be rife in the sport. In the past, many players have had to pay the price for choosing to cut corners. In South Africa, some development structures seem to be still grappling with age cheats. Age fraud is also seen as a taboo topic by many footballers, who chose not to speak about the subject. eNCA’s Ronald Masinda has more in this special report. Watch the video below for the full story. eNCA